You can use either of the following options:

* Include all the properties which you need in the list (including `CLB`). Then after assigning the list as [`DataSource`](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.windows.forms.datagridview.datasource?WT.mc_id=DT-MVP-5003235) of the [`DataGridView`](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.windows.forms.datagridview?WT.mc_id=DT-MVP-5003235), hide the corresponding column:
  
        advancedDataGridView.DataSource = list;
        advancedDataGridView.Columns[&quot;CLB&quot;].Visible = false;


* Create a model class containing all the properties which you need, including `CLB`. Then just decorate `CLB` with `[Browsable(false)]` attribute. (You need to select the result by creating instance of the model class, rather than anonymous type.)

        [Browsable(false)]
